  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the bulgur is cooking, sprinkle the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> over a chopping board with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Press the<strong> chicken breast portions </strong>onto the seasoning so that they're evenly coated – this is your <strong>seasoned chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until browned</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crumble the<strong> Greek cheese </strong>into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>crumbled Greek cheese</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>rocket</strong> to a large bowl and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken</strong> has browned, reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Cut the <strong>nectarines</strong> in half lengthways, around the <strong>stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and remove using a spoon, then roughly chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with the <strong>fig relish</strong>, 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>figgy dressing</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped nectarine</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> cooked</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>bulgur</strong> and <strong>warmed nectarine</strong> to the bowl with the rocket, Greek cheese and spring onion<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix – this is your <strong>nectarine & Greek cheese salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1027.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
